 MBOMBELA – The road leading to the University of Mpumalanga has been re-opened and protesters have been dispersed, according to Capt. Dawie Pretorius of SAPS. This follows protest action by a group of disgruntled people earlier this morning, who according to Pretorius are unhappy because they allege that contractors are employing foreign nationals. “The protesting people want local contractors who are busy with construction work at the University to hire local people, and not foreign nationals,” said Pretorius. MBOMBELA – A group of approximately sixty people are protesting at the University of Mpumalanga. The gates to the university are locked, and it has been confirmed that SAPS and private security companies are on the scene. This is a developing story and Lowvelder will keep you updated as soon as new information becomes available.